caption: Overpriced for what it was. Food was decent though.
My top place for quality cafe food. Don't worry if it's busy, it is worth the wait. Next time I'll be back with my relatives. The bill was reasonable.

The food here was amazing. We got here about 8:45 a.m. on a Monday morning and it was packed. We waited about 5 minutes to be sat at the big round communal table. Service was quick and the staff was friendly. I had the sausage and cheese biscuit with cheddar and tomato jam (pictured). It was divine. The crispy garlic potatoes it comes with were also delicious. My husband got an almond croissant (soft and warm) and scrambled eggs and he had no complaints.
Good food and ambiance
Lovely food, fantastic breakfast parfait
Delicious food! Great macchiato, decent price.
nice and cozy breakfast spot.
One of the best places to have a tasty breakfast and specialty coffee. Friendly atmosphere.
Good eggs Benedict with biscuit instead of muffin.  Very good cottage-like potatoes.  Very good staff.

I did a lot of good eatin’ during my week in New Orleans, but I must say that breakfast at Silver Whistle Cafe was a standout meal! The atmosphere was delightful - historic charm with just enough modern taste. The coffee was some of the best I had in NOLA. Even seemingly simple dishes had a remarkable quality; for instance, the breakfast parfait was perfection. I usually don’t order this sort of dish in a restaurant since it’s easy to assemble at home, and prepared versions are usually too sweet. But this was better than any parfait I’ve ever made! The granola tasted homey and intensely nutty, and was layered with thick unsweetened yogurt and fresh fruit. The balance between crunchy/creamy and tangy/sweet was ideal. The egg white frittata didn’t sound especially exciting on paper, but it was amazingly flavorful while still being light. And again, the textural counterpoint offered by fresh greens and radishes made things interesting & balanced. The service was speedy and friendly, too. Overall, it was an easy-going and lip-smacking start to the day!
Absolutely wonderful experience here! Great food in a really compfy setting that allowed me and my family to sit back and really enjoy a lovely breakfast.
Oatmeal was fantastic! The grapefruit  brulee was amazing. Also, amazing photo op in the sitting area next door next to the bathrooms.

Great food at moderate prices, friendly personell and non dairy milk options (oatmilk!) was available.  One thing that joyed me most was the kids weren’t handed disposables right away! This place has class!  We were so pleased with their breakfast. We had waffles and eggs benedict. The benedicts were served with a homemade hollandaise on the perfectly runny poached eggs along well balanced seasoned breakfast potatoes and a freshly baked buttermilk biscuit.
Went there every morning on our short trip to NO, fell in love with their American breakfasts
Wonderful breakfast and cocktails. The service is always on point and the staff is friendly.

This place can get busy so be prepared to share the large table with other diners if you arrive when it's crowded! The coffee was decent. The food was mixed. Everything was edible and arrived quickly, but the biscuit wasn't as moist and crumbly as I'd expect, it tasted like it'd been baked the previous day and toasted after I ordered it. They served a bruleed grapefruit half which was a great idea and tasted good but was impossible to eat because they didn't provide a grapefruit spoon or other utensils that would've made extracting the grapefruit easy.  The service was excellent. The waiters were very attentive.
Nice staff. Wish the menu had more options.
Brilliant staff, great food
I wasn't expecting the food to be as good as it was. We had eggs, sausage, potatoes and toast. It was all good. The staff was great too.
Quaint little place to catch a bite during the day. Very quick service, very friendly staff. Reasonable prices.
Great breakfast, prompt service.  Had pecan waffle, and their classic breakfast; both were great.
Egg white frittata was awesome. Quiet cafe in the Garden District.
Food is good, wait staff is good, all around Pleasant experience
Great food in an adorable environment
Very good place
Great service, delectable pastries and a spot on Cortado started my Monday off with a smile!
Good food!
Excellent service and food
Everything came out cold lol 🤷.  But my server was very nice.  Very small menu...
Too expensive. 2 cups of reg coffee and 2 danish... $15..only for special occasions..not my daily spot.
The food was good a small menu
Great breakfast along the Garden District line. Loved the benedict!
Fantastic. Super cute small casual breakfast diner. Breakfast po boy was delicious. Friendly service, quick wait time and affordable.
Lovely, friendly staff, super convenient to our hotel, great coffee, delicious sparkly brownie.
Great cafe! Delish breakfast! I especially loved their biscuits. The staff was friendly and made me feel at home.

Service was slow, the eggs Benedict yokes were hard boiled with stiff, flavorless hollandise sauce on a dry biscuit, we expected more.  Very disappointing AND expensive on our last day in town. Try the quiche down the street at Avenue Cafe, you won't be disappointed!
Food was delicious! Just a bit pricey. I paid $20 for a iced coffee and this filling breakfast poboys
Cute little cafe in Pontchartrain hotel on St. Charles.  Great coffee and waffles.  More substantial breakfast options are available. Service is friendly and fast.

One of the top breakfast spots in town. I personally like this place because of it's food and the portion that they provide. Not a big cafe, there are few seats and a community table bit the place is so sweet. You would definitely enjoy your time here.

This was one of our best meals. We came for Sunday dinner in late September and were the only diners in the establishment. We both got the fish (one special, one almondine) and both dishes were to die for. Service was really great as well.
I don’t usually leave reviews. But I came for breakfast and had the best breakfast of life. Thank you.
Just had a coffee but it hit the spot. Great location and friendly staff.
Lovely service and delicious coffee!

We are here on Thanksgiving Day. Small cafe with community table and couple seats.  Portions are large as in the carbs...bread, potatoes.etc My bf got eggs, hashbrown,  bacon and side of toast. I just got eggs and bacon. The hasbrowns are more like potatoes being overcooked to give them a crunch. We got 4 pieces of large thick bacon each. Eggs were delicious. Overall good cost $25. Which I personallly think is high.
We were walking along St. Charles Avenue looking for breakfast. We decided to give Silver Whistle Cafe a try. The food was delicious but we waited 25 minutes for foods.

The Silver Whistle Cafe is a great place to pick up a coffee and pastry before taking a walking tour of NOLA's Garden District. Selection is limited and service is brusque but everything available is quality and delicious.
The portions were large, and the food was okay.  The ceiling was beautiful.   The service was mediocre at best. We would not eat here again.
The staff was awful and so was the food unless you are related to one of the staff you will get horrible service
The coffee here is amazing, the staff is friendly and attentive, and the way they cook the eggs is perfect. I definitely recommend the NOLA breakfast with a cup of coffee!
Best grits to infinity and beyond

I was disappointed to miss the breakfast menu, but settled for the grilled cheese and it was excellent. Delicious cheese with shimeji mushrooms with some garlic marinera sauce for dipping. On the smaller side, but one of the best grilled cheeses I’ve ever had. Coffee was good too. Staff was very friendly as well.

Love this spot. Excellent food and this morning, excellent company too. Sat at the community table and had great conversations. The service is always expedient, food delicious. One of the best cups of coffee.
Very casual breakfast, brunchl place in Garden district
Slow service food ok.
Food was colder than I like
The food was excellent and the staff very attentive.

A historic wonder brought back to life and worth it just for the gorgeous interior (also check out the bar across the hotel lobby as it's hand painted bayou murals are fabulous too). The grits are stone ground and substantial. A true historic recipe that makes them absolutely delicious without adding cheese or anything else. I loved them. Also the hash browns are cooked in duck fat and delicious. Don't write them off. I had the pimento cheese omelette because weight gain be damned, I want a decadent culinary adventure, and I was in no way disappointed.
Great food and service, but very expensive. Free coffee refills with your breakfast, though.
Good food near our motel
Small cozy cafe.  Great pecan waffles.
Wonderful little breakfast place we ran across while going somewhere else. Great eggs benedict, great breakfast po-boy and excellent coffee. The maple Danish was awesome. Top Notch service too.
Great lates
Great breakfast spot.... very friendly staff!
Honey biscuit was so yummy!
Delicious and very large portions. Also very accommodating with substitutions.

The hash browns were perfectly balanced with scallions and are super crispy and wonderful. What a lovely lunch! My fiancee also thought the bacon was cooked to perfection. Not too limp and not too crispy.

Great NOLA breakfast. The hash browns and grits are some of the best I've had. But as mentioned, the prices are reflective of being connected to an upscale hotel. 5 stars for food/service,  3 stars for value
The Silver Whistle Cafe was a delicious breakfast. I had the special, Eggs & Ratatouille with a side of hash browns. A bit on the higher end for breakfast but it was worth it!!! Hats off to the chef!
Good breakfast cafe...good coffee and good food.  Try the blueberry muffin.
The best grits I have ever had in my life! Sausage was spicy, eggs were cooked perfectly, one great breakfast!

Located off the lobby of the Pontchartrain Hotel, the Silver Whistle Café is convenient to the Wyndham Avenue Plaza Resort and Josephine stop on the St Charles trolley line. Start with some excellent coffee while you contemplate what you want for breakfast. The menu is simple, yet varied enough that you could enjoy something different several days. The Blue Crab Pimento Cheese omelet I had was outstanding, but the delicious bowl of creamy stone ground grits stole the show! Service was great and the prices were also very reasonable. Can't wait to return on our next trip to NOLA.
Best eggs benedict I've had. Should be listed as $$, though - brunch entrees are up to $16.
Nice breakfast. NOLA breakfast is fine

Stopped in for lunch when I first arrived in New Orleans. Very nice service, atmosphere was a bit quieter than I expected, coffee was excellent and the ham/cheddar biscuit was delicious! I would definitely return!

(Translated by Google) The Silver Whistle is the bar of the Hotel Pontarchtrain, but it can be accessed without being a guest directly from the sidewalk or inside the hotel. The place is beautifully decorated, like an old diner, but with very good taste. The attention from the staff was impeccable and they prepared delicious and very good quality dishes. It is located on Saint Charles Avenue, in the Garden District of NOLA and is ideal for a lunch break or for breakfast.  (Original) El Silver Whistle el bar del Hotel Pontarchtrain, pero se puede acceder sin ser huésped directamente desde la acera o por dentro del hotel. El lugar esta hermosamente decorado, como si fuera un antiguo diner, pero con muy buen gusto. La atención por parte del personal fue impecable y nos prepararon platos deliciosos y de muy buena calidad. Esta ubicado sobre la av Saint Charles, en el Garden District de NOLA y es ideal para una pausa al mediodía o para desayunar.

Service and food are excellent. Establishment is very clean and space is well designed. Prices are not based in reality. $14 for a small bowl of salad. Clearly here for well to do guests of attached upscale hotel. Don't bother if you plan on walking in off the street.
Super friendly service with good coffee in a great location. The baked treats are also diverse and delicious. Check them out!
